==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[kilomètre]] < Greek [[χίλιοι]] ('[[thousand]]') + [[μέτρον]].

===Pronunciation===
''American English'' — {{IPA|/kɪləmiɾɚ/}}

===Alternative spellings===
*(''British, Canadian, etc.'') [[kilometre]]

===Noun===
'''kilometer''' (''US spelling''; ''plural:'' '''[[kilometers]]''')

# An [[SI#Abbreviation|SI]]/MKS unit of measure equal to one thousand [[meter]]s.

====Symbol====
*[[km]] (''official [[SI]] symbol''), [[Km]] (''chiefly American, in nonscientific usage, such as in road signs'')

